1 SECTION 3. There is appropriated the sum of three million five hundred twenty
2 thousand dollars ($3,520,000) in recurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to the State
3 Auditor to create a financial administration program. This program shall provide the resources
4 to employ 32 additional finance professionals to assist small local governments and public
5 authorities with returning to a compliant status, with priority for local governments and public
6 authorities with limited means and those local governments or public authorities on the Unit
7 Assistance List published by the Local Government Commission annually.
8 SECTION 4. This act becomes effective July 1, 2025, and applies to audits
9 conducted on or after that date.
